# Trivy baseline -- gate-on-new: accept CURRENT HIGH/CRITICAL findings; the build
# trivy gate fails only on a NEW fixed-available CVE. Trimmed 2026-07-13 (SMP-1297 /
# Forgejo #474) against a live trivy scan of the deployed image: 70 stale entries
# removed (no longer present -- fixed by the chamber source-build (#291) + apt-upgrade
# in the runtime stage since the #674 refresh, incl. libmariadb3 / CVE-2025-13699).
#
# SMP-1297 remediation: activestorage/activesupport (Rails 7.2.3.1), faraday,
# fast-xml-parser, puma (7.2.1), uri (0.13.3) and zlib (3.2.3) were pulled forward
# and their CVEs removed from this baseline. The entries below map to gems/npm pkgs
# that already sit at a fixed version in the CURRENT lockfiles (stale from the older
# image scan), so they should no longer appear once the image rebuilds. They are kept
# here until a fresh image-scan-validated pass confirms their absence (form-data has a
# nested-vs-top-level nuance). Remediation tracked in #474. pkg -> fixed version:
#   braces: 3.0.3
#   erb: ~> 4.0.3.1, ~> 4.0.4.1, ~> 6.0.1.1, >= 6.0.4
